dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha c Kulasekara b Maharoof 25 (35b 2x4 0x6 63m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: gone!! Maharoof has been gifted a wicket here, that was pitched full on middle and off, Chibhabha came down the track and tried to loft it over mid on, got the leading edge and Kulasekara at mid on ran back a few steps to take a well judged catch. There was no need for that shot but Chibhabha lost his concentration there!

commentTextItems.html: that's it! it's all over!,that was tossed up on middle and leg, Sangakkara came down the track and lofted it over the bowlers head for a one-bounce four to the long on boundary

commentPostTextItems.html: The end of a one-sided affair. It would perhaps not have been one had Matsikenyeri and Taibu continued playing the way the were. Instead, their team capitulated to spin to lose seven wickets for three runs and make a Sri Lankan win a formality after being bowled out for 127. Sri Lanka, who are without Jayasuriya, took their time to chase down the target, trying to get acclimatised to the conditions in Zimbabwe before the four other games to follow.
Ray Price and Prosper Utseya bowled well but just didn't have enough runs on the board to put pressure on Sri Lanka. Hope the next game turns out to be more competitive.
Prosper Utseya: "We are disappointed not to get a competitive score."
Mahela Jayawardene: "We wanted to win the first game, but were disappointed with the way we started. However, our spinners did a wonderful job."
Muttiah Muralitharan is the Man of the Match.
Well, that's it from here folks. Join us for the second ODI on Saturday. Goodbye

dismissalText.commentary: Vusi Sibanda c Kapugedera b Kulasekara 9 (24b 2x4 0x6 41m) SR: 37.5

dismissalComment.html: on a good length on the off and swinging in, tries to defend it on the back foot, gets a thick outside edge straight to Kapugedara at second slip who takes a comfortable catch. One down!

headshotImage.caption: Thilan Thushara  player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Thilan Thushara  player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza run out (Tharanga) 15 (32b 3x4 0x6 58m) SR: 46.87

dismissalComment.html: runout, good length on the off stump, defended to cover, Chibabha calls for the single but sends Masakdza back only after he is almost halfway down the pitch, Tharanga at cover fields well and throws down the stumps at the non-strikers end with an under-arm flick to find Masakdza short of his ground

headshotImage.caption: Farveez Maharoof player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Farveez Maharoof player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha c Kulasekara b Maharoof 25 (35b 2x4 0x6 63m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: gone!! Maharoof has been gifted a wicket here, that was pitched full on middle and off, Chibhabha came down the track and tried to loft it over mid on, got the leading edge and Kulasekara at mid on ran back a few steps to take a well judged catch. There was no need for that shot but Chibhabha lost his concentration there!

headshotImage.caption: Muttiah Muralitharan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Muttiah Muralitharan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri b Muralidaran 21 (20b 0x4 1x6 21m) SR: 105

dismissalComment.html: bowled 'im!! That was pitched on a good length on the off and spinning in, too close to cut, Matsinkinyeri gets on the back foot and looks to guide that wide of short third-man, gets an inside edge onto the off stump

headshotImage.caption: Muttiah Muralitharan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Muttiah Muralitharan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura lbw b Muralidaran 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: gone! bowled flat and quick on middle and leg from round the wicket, pitches on a good length and straightens, Chigumbura comes forward to defend but makes no contact with the bat, struck low on the pads, Murali goes up, and the umpire raises his finger. That would have gone on to hit middle and leg

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga run out (Mpofu) 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

stories.title: Sri Lanka dominant but captain looks for improvement
stories.subTitle: Zimbabwe v Sri Lanka, 1st ODI, Harare
stories.summary: Despite his team claiming a comprehensive six-wicket win over Zimbabwe in the opening ODI, the Sri Lanka captain Mahela Jayawardene is still looking for improvement

stories.title: Murali and Mendis rout Zimbabwe

stories.summary: Zimbabwe tumbled from 124 for 3 to 127 in the blink of an eye, leaving Sri Lanka to coast to their target with six wickets and more than 16 overs in hand
